ts, surveys and one-on-one interviews, Scherer illuminates the complicated relationship between diversity and court legitimacy. She shows us how diverse representation can positively impact perceptions of the court among women and racial minorities, while having a negative impact on the perceptions among white people and men. Ultimately, Diversifying the Courts provides insight into the impact of gender, race, and ethnicity on the courts, illuminating some of the major challenges facing the American judicial system in the years that lie ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLAW / Government / General.2bisacsh  aBlack Judicial Appointments.  aBlack judges.  aCourt Appointments.  aCourt Diversity.  aDescriptive Race Representation.  aDescriptive Representation.  aDiversification Strategies.  aDiversity Debate.  aFederal Judges.  aFemale Judicial Appointments.  aGender Representation.  aGovernment Benefits.  aGroup Membership.  aJudicial Appointments.  aJudicial Decision-Making.  aJudicial Diversity.  aJudicial Legitimacy.  aMarginalized Groups.  aParty Identification.  aPerceptions of Legitimacy.  aPolitical Legitimacy.  aPublic Opinion.  aRacial Diversity.  aRacial Representation.  aRacial and Gender Diversity.  aRepresentational Politics.  aSubstantive Representation.  aWhite judges.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075163540uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479818754.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479818754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479818754/original  a978-3-11-075163-5  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEB